(Focusing on Seung Ho)

528
00:18:32,327 --> 00:18:33,327
Will it be successful?

529
00:18:33,857 --> 00:18:35,426
- That's a good one. - "Will it be successful?"

530
00:18:35,427 --> 00:18:37,327
(I'm so curious.)

531
00:18:38,067 --> 00:18:39,426
- Okay. What does it say? - All right.

532
00:18:39,427 --> 00:18:41,813
(What's the answer to his question about the show's success?)

533
00:18:41,837 --> 00:18:44,167
(I believe in you, Almighty Seung Ho.)

534
00:18:44,367 --> 00:18:46,336
- "Empty your mind." - "Empty your mind."

535
00:18:46,337 --> 00:18:47,337
- It means we should relax. - So...

536
00:18:47,338 --> 00:18:48,376
"Empty your mind."

537
00:18:48,377 --> 00:18:49,736
So it means there's no pressure.

538
00:18:49,737 --> 00:18:51,036
It means we should go back to the basics.

539
00:18:51,037 --> 00:18:53,006
- When we fully enjoy ourselves, - Right.

540
00:18:53,007 --> 00:18:55,377
- success will follow. - That's right.

541
00:18:56,147 --> 00:18:57,346
- Let's stop. - Right.

542
00:18:57,347 --> 00:18:58,347
(I won't look. This has nothing to do with me.)

543
00:18:58,348 --> 00:18:59,846
Let me pull out one more.

544
00:18:59,847 --> 00:19:00,847
Sure.

545
00:19:00,848 --> 00:19:02,063
(They're having fun with Euratgotcha.)

546
00:19:02,087 --> 00:19:03,387
- Wanna Base. - Gosh.

547
00:19:04,017 --> 00:19:05,227
Wanna Base.

548
00:19:05,657 --> 00:19:06,657
(Ringing)

549
00:19:06,927 --> 00:19:07,997
Ding-dong.

550
00:19:08,597 --> 00:19:09,597
More people came.

551
00:19:09,598 --> 00:19:10,926
- Let me go and check. - Hello.

552
00:19:10,927 --> 00:19:12,597
(Who are their next guests?)

553
00:19:13,497 --> 00:19:15,366
- This is quite a jump. - Hello.

554
00:19:15,367 --> 00:19:16,797
Min Hyuk is here too.

555
00:19:16,867 --> 00:19:18,866
(BTOB completed the 3rd generation of K-pop with Wanna One.)

556
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:20,366
("BTOB's Comeback Will Go Toe to Toe with Highlight and Wanna One")

557
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:22,513
("BTOB's Comeback Was Successful, Topping The 6 Music Charts")

558
00:19:22,537 --> 00:19:25,246
(Today's guest and the main rapper of BTOB, Min Hyuk, )

559
00:19:25,247 --> 00:19:28,976
(met Woo Jin, another main rapper, on a radio show.)

560
00:19:28,977 --> 00:19:31,077
(They've been close friends ever since then.)

561
00:19:31,387 --> 00:19:32,387
(More guests come in.)

562
00:19:32,388 --> 00:19:33,786
- My gosh. - Yes.

563
00:19:33,787 --> 00:19:34,787
(LEO and XINLONG of ALPHA DRIVE ONE)

564
00:19:34,788 --> 00:19:36,287
Hello.

565
00:19:36,487 --> 00:19:38,056
- It's ALD1. - ALD1.

566
00:19:38,057 --> 00:19:39,057
- Hey, LEO. - Hello.

567
00:19:39,887 --> 00:19:42,356
(During the 2026 Visionary Awards in February)

568
00:19:42,357 --> 00:19:44,966
(The members of Wanna One came to congratulate Min Hyun.)

569
00:19:44,967 --> 00:19:46,727
(They were spotted saying hello to someone.)

570
00:19:46,797 --> 00:19:48,566
These guys are from ALD1.

571
00:19:48,567 --> 00:19:50,466
- Hello. - Congratulations on your debut.

572
00:19:50,467 --> 00:19:52,067
Do you want to be on our show?

573
00:19:52,307 --> 00:19:54,436
- Sure. Please invite us. - Okay. Bye.

574
00:19:54,437 --> 00:19:55,906
(They said goodbye after making a promise.)

575
00:19:55,907 --> 00:19:59,176
Of course, I love Wanna One.

576
00:19:59,177 --> 00:20:00,307
I'm also a Wannable.

577
00:20:00,907 --> 00:20:02,387
- We're Wannables. - We're Wannables.

578
00:20:02,747 --> 00:20:04,686
- Special guests are here. - Right.

579
00:20:04,687 --> 00:20:07,416
- Please come on in. - Let's sit down.

580
00:20:07,417 --> 00:20:08,456
This place is huge.

581
00:20:08,457 --> 00:20:09,516
- Seriously? - What? I don't know.

582
00:20:09,517 --> 00:20:11,087
Gosh, no way.

583
00:20:11,427 --> 00:20:12,456
Have you been well?

584
00:20:12,457 --> 00:20:13,756
- Gosh. - Have you been well?

585
00:20:13,757 --> 00:20:15,157
- Yes. - It's been a while.

586
00:20:15,727 --> 00:20:17,026
- Please sit down. - Please sit down.

587
00:20:17,027 --> 00:20:19,396
- Okay. Thank you. - Sit in the middle.

588
00:20:19,397 --> 00:20:21,227
(Arranging their seats)

589
00:20:21,327 --> 00:20:23,036
Thank you for coming. Aren't you busy?

590
00:20:23,037 --> 00:20:24,037
- Gosh, no problem. - They're super busy.

591
00:20:24,038 --> 00:20:25,236
They're getting ready for their comeback.

592
00:20:25,237 --> 00:20:26,466
We need to go back to our practice later.

593
00:20:26,467 --> 00:20:27,906
- Really? You made time for us? - We...

594
00:20:27,907 --> 00:20:30,206
- We really wanted to come here. - Really?

595
00:20:30,207 --> 00:20:32,646
- Really? The rest of them didn't? - We insisted on coming here.

596
00:20:32,647 --> 00:20:33,647
What?

597
00:20:33,648 --> 00:20:35,568
- Oh, Sung Woon. - Only you guys wanted to come?

598
00:20:35,777 --> 00:20:36,916
Did everyone try to get out of this?

599
00:20:36,917 --> 00:20:38,546
- "You should go." - We're actually the winners.

600
00:20:38,547 --> 00:20:40,946
Actually, I watched LEO...

601
00:20:40,947 --> 00:20:42,886
- perform on stage as a solo artist. - Yes.

602
00:20:42,887 --> 00:20:44,356
- He performed on a music show. - Yes, only briefly.

603
00:20:44,357 --> 00:20:46,256
- He was fantastic on stage. - Gosh.

604
00:20:46,257 --> 00:20:47,286
- He's so talented. - Gosh.

605
00:20:47,287 --> 00:20:50,996
Back then, I thought to myself that he would go to places.

606
00:20:50,997 --> 00:20:52,466
- I remember how talented he was... - Thank you.

607
00:20:52,467 --> 00:20:54,096
When we were active around the same time.

608
00:20:54,097 --> 00:20:55,097
Right. We were active around the same time.

609
00:20:55,098 --> 00:20:56,596
Yes. When his group made their debut,

610
00:20:56,597 --> 00:20:59,236
I said, "Yes. I knew he would make it."

611
00:20:59,237 --> 00:21:00,506
- Thank you. - Look at his ears.

612
00:21:00,507 --> 00:21:02,306
- They're super red. - They're red.

613
00:21:02,307 --> 00:21:03,906
- Compliments make him shy. - Thank you.

614
00:21:03,907 --> 00:21:05,387
You had that experienced senior vibe.

615
00:21:05,677 --> 00:21:07,376
Well, I do have seniority here.

616
00:21:07,377 --> 00:21:08,416
(The generation integration of idol groups)

617
00:21:08,417 --> 00:21:09,417
He's also your senior.

618
00:21:10,747 --> 00:21:12,846
You had that senior vibe in spades.

619
00:21:12,847 --> 00:21:15,186
"I knew you'd make it."

620
00:21:15,187 --> 00:21:17,616
- "I knew you'd make it." That's... - "I knew you'd make it."

621
00:21:17,617 --> 00:21:19,056
- "I knew you'd make it." - It meant to say...

622
00:21:19,057 --> 00:21:21,356
I was rooting for him with a lot of support.

623
00:21:21,357 --> 00:21:22,797
Thank you so much.

624
00:21:23,097 --> 00:21:24,727
I'll behave myself now.

625
00:21:25,227 --> 00:21:26,366
(Adoring him)

626
00:21:26,367 --> 00:21:29,436
Have you watched our show before?

627
00:21:29,437 --> 00:21:30,666
Our season from a decade ago.

628
00:21:30,667 --> 00:21:31,836
- The one from a decade ago? - Yes.

629
00:21:31,837 --> 00:21:35,106
You guys were super famous back then.

630
00:21:35,107 --> 00:21:36,306
I watched all of your performances,

631
00:21:36,307 --> 00:21:38,347
- but not your reality show. - Right.

632
00:21:39,347 --> 00:21:40,807
All those years ago,

633
00:21:41,347 --> 00:21:42,616
I hated you guys.

634
00:21:42,617 --> 00:21:43,816
Really?

635
00:21:43,817 --> 00:21:45,086
Why did you hate us?

636
00:21:45,087 --> 00:21:47,246
- "Hate" is such a strong word. - Yes.

637
00:21:47,247 --> 00:21:48,387
I was...

638
00:21:49,017 --> 00:21:50,687
kind of jealous.

639
00:21:51,087 --> 00:21:53,456
I was trying my best to survive in this industry.

640
00:21:53,457 --> 00:21:54,726
A group of such talented people...

641
00:21:54,727 --> 00:21:55,956
- joined the scene. - We came out of the blue.

642
00:21:55,957 --> 00:21:57,756
So we were a bit jealous.

643
00:21:57,757 --> 00:21:59,877
I'm talking about the other groups from the same era.

644
00:21:59,997 --> 00:22:01,736
At first, it was jealousy.

645
00:22:01,737 --> 00:22:04,436
You guys decided to go separate ways...

646
00:22:04,437 --> 00:22:06,736
only after a short run.

647
00:22:06,737 --> 00:22:08,337
I was sad to hear about that.

648
00:22:09,077 --> 00:22:11,947
When I heard about your reunion, I was so happy.

649
00:22:13,307 --> 00:22:14,676
Thank you.

650
00:22:14,677 --> 00:22:15,976
It means we have people supporting us.

651
00:22:15,977 --> 00:22:18,316
It brought back old memories from all those years ago.

652
00:22:18,317 --> 00:22:20,346
- Right. - It gave me...

653
00:22:20,347 --> 00:22:23,687
all kinds of feelings. I was so happy to hear the news.

654
00:22:24,187 --> 00:22:25,826
Everyone worked so hard.

655
00:22:25,827 --> 00:22:27,387
(He wants to root for their new start.)

656
00:22:27,527 --> 00:22:29,826
Having people we know at the Wanna Base...

657
00:22:29,827 --> 00:22:32,066
- feels like a housewarming party. - Exactly.

658
00:22:32,067 --> 00:22:34,666
Isn't this the first time we ever had guests over?

659
00:22:34,667 --> 00:22:35,737
Right.

660
00:22:36,267 --> 00:22:38,137
(At that moment...)

661
00:22:39,437 --> 00:22:42,907
(A man is approaching the gate while exuding a grand vibe.)

662
00:22:44,377 --> 00:22:45,477
(Ringing)

663
00:22:47,847 --> 00:22:48,877
(Ringing)

664
00:22:49,717 --> 00:22:50,746
We have another guest.

665
00:22:50,747 --> 00:22:52,347
- Another guest? - There's someone here.

666
00:22:52,417 --> 00:22:53,946
- Wait. - I'm getting scared now.

667
00:22:53,947 --> 00:22:55,057
Wait.

668
00:22:58,017 --> 00:23:00,587
(Are you there?)

669
00:23:00,887 --> 00:23:04,497
(Checking)

670
00:23:04,897 --> 00:23:07,396
(He tries to find a way to open the door himself.)

671
00:23:07,397 --> 00:23:10,067
(Is anyone in here?)

672
00:23:10,537 --> 00:23:14,107
(Fighting with the vending machine door in a cute way)

673
00:23:18,577 --> 00:23:22,177
(In the end, he lets himself in.)

674
00:23:22,447 --> 00:23:25,386
- I'll go out and check. - We're running out of chairs now.

675
00:23:25,387 --> 00:23:27,447
Wait, those are a woman's ankles.

676
00:23:27,747 --> 00:23:29,856
(The owner of slender ankles arrives at the entrance.)

677
00:23:29,857 --> 00:23:31,387
- It can't be BoA, right? - What?

678
00:23:32,187 --> 00:23:33,227
What?

679
00:23:33,857 --> 00:23:34,897
What?

680
00:23:35,427 --> 00:23:36,927
Hey!

681
00:23:37,557 --> 00:23:39,026
- Hey! - Who is it?

682
00:23:39,027 --> 00:23:40,597
What is it?

683
00:23:41,197 --> 00:23:43,296
- Hello. - What? No way!

684
00:23:43,297 --> 00:23:44,496
- Ji Hoon! - Ji Hoon!

685
00:23:44,497 --> 00:23:46,336
- Ji Hoon! You have to come out. - Ji Hoon!

686
00:23:46,337 --> 00:23:48,306
(The introvert, Ji Hoon, is trying to read the situation.)

687
00:23:48,307 --> 00:23:49,476
- Ji Hoon! - Ji Hoon!

688
00:23:49,477 --> 00:23:50,576
- Ji Hoon! - Hey.

689
00:23:50,577 --> 00:23:51,746
- Ji Hoon! - Ji Hoon!

690
00:23:51,747 --> 00:23:53,246
- Ji Hoon! - You have to come out.

691
00:23:53,247 --> 00:23:55,617
(Why are you calling me?)

692
00:23:55,847 --> 00:23:57,477
(Striding over)

693
00:23:57,747 --> 00:23:59,647
My gosh!

694
00:24:00,217 --> 00:24:03,017
(Why did the members frantically call Ji Hoon?)

695
00:24:03,317 --> 00:24:04,486
- Hello. - Hey.

696
00:24:04,487 --> 00:24:06,827
(Director Jang Hang Jun of "The King's Warden" is here!)

697
00:24:07,357 --> 00:24:08,357
- Gosh. - Hello.

698
00:24:08,358 --> 00:24:09,496
- What? No way! - Hello.

699
00:24:09,497 --> 00:24:13,466
(The great director dives in without hesitation.)

700
00:24:13,467 --> 00:24:15,967
(This is the thrill of being at the Wanna Base.)

701
00:24:16,367 --> 00:24:17,736
(Oh, my goodness.)

702
00:24:17,737 --> 00:24:19,166
- Director Jang. - Gosh.

703
00:24:19,167 --> 00:24:20,636
This is... Sir.

704
00:24:20,637 --> 00:24:22,206
- You didn't have to jump. - What?

705
00:24:22,207 --> 00:24:24,006
- You didn't have to jump. - My gosh.

706
00:24:24,007 --> 00:24:25,976
- We'll take care of them. - Okay.

707
00:24:25,977 --> 00:24:27,046
You didn't have to.

708
00:24:27,047 --> 00:24:28,946
- Sir. - Ji Hoon.

709
00:24:28,947 --> 00:24:31,476
(Hang Jun and Ji Hoon finally meet.)

710
00:24:31,477 --> 00:24:33,016
- Hello. - Hello.

711
00:24:33,017 --> 00:24:35,457
- What? - Hello.

712
00:24:36,187 --> 00:24:38,357
- Hello. - My goodness.

713
00:24:38,627 --> 00:24:40,527
- Please sit down. - Please sit.

714
00:24:41,327 --> 00:24:44,627
(The unexpected guest also surprises Ji Hoon.)

715
00:24:45,067 --> 00:24:46,196
I got the chills.

716
00:24:46,197 --> 00:24:47,227
- Right. - Ji Hoon.

717
00:24:47,467 --> 00:24:49,796
- Gosh, Ji Hoon. - Ji Hoon, sit next to him.

718
00:24:49,797 --> 00:24:51,336
Right here.

719
00:24:51,337 --> 00:24:53,237
- Have you been well? - Yes.

720
00:24:53,407 --> 00:24:56,837
- I heard about your reunion. - Yes.

721
00:24:58,177 --> 00:25:01,976
(It was during the VIP screening the members attended in January.)

722
00:25:01,977 --> 00:25:03,716
(Ji Hoon introduced Wanna One at the screening.)

723
00:25:03,717 --> 00:25:06,947
(Saving Wanna One in his memory)

724
00:25:07,617 --> 00:25:10,657
(Great Director Hang Jun came to congratulate their reunion.)

725
00:25:10,787 --> 00:25:12,356
Is this your cheering stick?

726
00:25:12,357 --> 00:25:13,557
(Is this your cheering stick?)

727
00:25:16,127 --> 00:25:18,967
I brought them as the housewarming presents.

728
00:25:19,467 --> 00:25:21,967
I thought they would look great here.

729
00:25:22,137 --> 00:25:24,536
- He... - These cups are custom-made.

730
00:25:24,537 --> 00:25:26,106
- I brought them for you. - Thank you.

731
00:25:26,107 --> 00:25:28,406
- He brought his merchandise. - Thank you.

732
00:25:28,407 --> 00:25:29,777
What an honor.

733
00:25:30,137 --> 00:25:31,277
Right here.

734
00:25:31,847 --> 00:25:33,887
(It also comes with a placard with his face on it.)

735
00:25:34,007 --> 00:25:35,646
(A mug, a cheering stick, and a placard)

736
00:25:35,647 --> 00:25:38,687
(A trio of Hang Jun's merchandise only for Wanna One)

737
00:25:39,647 --> 00:25:42,556
You brought your merchandise as a present?

738
00:25:42,557 --> 00:25:43,886
- Yes. - This one is so funny.

739
00:25:43,887 --> 00:25:45,056
It says...

740
00:25:45,057 --> 00:25:46,226
- This one is so funny. - It says...

741
00:25:46,227 --> 00:25:47,956
"A mug from Hang Jun, the great director..."

742
00:25:47,957 --> 00:25:49,826
"who made history in the movie industry of Korea."

743
00:25:49,827 --> 00:25:51,156
- Thank you. - It's an honor.

744
00:25:51,157 --> 00:25:52,597
- Thank you. - Thank you.

745
00:25:53,327 --> 00:25:56,767
- Thank you. - Congratulations.

746
00:25:57,167 --> 00:25:59,437
(His mug will go into the Food Zone.)

747
00:25:59,867 --> 00:26:02,876
(An unprecedented presence)

748
00:26:02,877 --> 00:26:05,023
(The cheering stick and placard will be in Ji Hoon's room.)

749
00:26:05,047 --> 00:26:07,447
(They've got their nice little spot.)

750
00:26:07,907 --> 00:26:11,077
Sir, you had many chances to see Ji Hoon lately, right?

751
00:26:11,547 --> 00:26:13,947
When was the last time we met?

752
00:26:14,817 --> 00:26:17,016
- It was... - The movie screening was...

753
00:26:17,017 --> 00:26:19,256
- Yes, that was it. - the last time we met.

754
00:26:19,257 --> 00:26:20,787
Ji Hoon...

755
00:26:21,387 --> 00:26:22,697
doesn't usually...

756
00:26:23,457 --> 00:26:24,657
reach out.

757
00:26:25,367 --> 00:26:26,426
Right. He's like that.

758
00:26:26,427 --> 00:26:27,767
Right. He rarely calls or texts.

759
00:26:27,997 --> 00:26:30,197
(The members already know about Ji Hoon's personality.)

760
00:26:30,237 --> 00:26:32,706
- I'm the same way. - I see.

761
00:26:32,707 --> 00:26:35,176
We don't call or text each other often. That works for me.

762
00:26:35,177 --> 00:26:36,406
I'm comfortable with that.

763
00:26:36,407 --> 00:26:37,706
- And... - Ji Hoon is like that.

764
00:26:37,707 --> 00:26:39,777
That suits my personality.

765
00:26:40,577 --> 00:26:41,677
You...

766
00:26:42,317 --> 00:26:43,676
gained weight a bit.

767
00:26:43,677 --> 00:26:44,677
Yes.

768
00:26:44,678 --> 00:26:46,987
(When he was in exile, when he's at the Wanna Base)

769
00:26:47,317 --> 00:26:49,217
(Laughing)

770
00:26:49,417 --> 00:26:51,757
- I'm on a break now. - Yes.

771
00:26:52,657 --> 00:26:53,986
(Ji Hoon's food wish list: Cotton candy)

772
00:26:53,987 --> 00:26:55,496
(Chinese food)

773
00:26:55,497 --> 00:26:56,996
(Pizza)

774
00:26:56,997 --> 00:26:58,496
(Spring cabbage bibimbap)

775
00:26:58,497 --> 00:26:59,896
(Buldak)

776
00:26:59,897 --> 00:27:01,327
(Slushy)

777
00:27:01,937 --> 00:27:03,937
(Ji Hoon is enjoying his break at the Wanna Base.)

778
00:27:04,097 --> 00:27:06,166
You must always try to lose weight.

779
00:27:06,167 --> 00:27:07,567
(His 2nd attack)

780
00:27:09,677 --> 00:27:10,977
(Laughing)

781
00:27:11,077 --> 00:27:12,246
You said that on a TV show.

782
00:27:12,247 --> 00:27:13,346
Right. I saw the interview.

783
00:27:13,347 --> 00:27:15,187
"He's not that handsome when he gains weight."

784
00:27:15,947 --> 00:27:17,376
(His nagging comes from love.)

785
00:27:17,377 --> 00:27:18,716
I laughed so hard at it.

786
00:27:18,717 --> 00:27:20,086
